Mages, though being top-DPS, and able to augment other casters/pets power, have zero defense, and are totally dependant on the group to keep them alive.<br>
Monks, having high damage, and also getting the pulling/safety FD-capabilities, miss defense power, and are onlyable to withstand damage for short amounts of time, or with greater group help.<br>
Enchanters, having extremely powerful Charms (not only PoP, they ever had), also bring the most risk to a group if they start this kind of damage.<br>
Wizards, having ultimately powerful short-term damage, and also the ability to evac, trade in any form of indirect damage or buffs or debuffs.<br>
Necromancers, while having superior mana regen, powerful pets, awesome DoT capabilities, snare and even FD, they miss the ability to increase their damage over short amounts of time like Magicians and Wizards can.<br>
and so on...and so on...<br>
<br>
There is really little left to rant about, it may be that the healing focus of clerics is often of more use than the damage power of a ranger, but every class has it's pro's and it's con's - just learn to use them in your groups.<br>
