<br>
That said, I'm a little miffed at some of the attitudes here.  &quot;whiney bitchy monk threads?&quot;  Are you kidding?  This is so ironic, I had to post something.<br>
<br>
You realize that this was EXACTLY the state of this board, and the magician board over at Casters Realm, not long ago, don't you?  People on other boards were laughing at &quot;those whiney, bitchy mages&quot; without having an inkling of understanding of the class or it's problems.  They had no clue of what made playing a mage a drag, or of all the problems we faced, as Kunark changed the playing field, eliminated the soloing, and in general, made being a mage a very hard thing.  Memories seem to be short around here.<br>
<br>
Now you're doing the exact same thing.  You haven't learned a damn thing, or are just too caught up in mage issues to empathize with the plight of another class or to objectively look at game balance or class balancing as a whole.  Do you really think that your pet should be outdamaging a rogue or monk, or be able to out-tank a warrior?  You do realize that real people play those classes, and would like to be viable contenders in the game, right?<br>
<br>
Grats mage community.  Now you can be known as the &quot;bragging, selfish told-you-so's&quot; instead of taking a better attitude and saying, &quot;hey, I bet monks might have a reason to bitch and whine....hell, we had our own reasons, not so long ago...&quot;<br>
<br>
Yes, the monk class is F'd up.  The other pure melees, the rogues and warriors, they have issues as well.  And all you can say is, &quot;well too bad, we had it bad, now it's their turn&quot;.  Well, with an attitude like that, don't bitch and moan and whine when you get nerfed and you see the pendulum swing again.  Because nobody will give a rat's ass and it will be no wonder.<br>
<br>
